com.bergerkiller.bukkit.common.nbt

Class CommonTagList

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bergerkiller.bukkit.common.wrappers.BasicWrapper<NBTBaseHandle>
      • com.bergerkiller.bukkit.common.nbt.CommonTag
        • com.bergerkiller.bukkit.common.nbt.CommonTagList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<CommonTag>, java.util.Collection<CommonTag>, java.util.List<CommonTag>

    public class CommonTagList
extends CommonTag
implements java.util.List<CommonTag>
    Data represents actual data stored by the tag. This can be:
    List, Map, byte, short, int, long, float, double, byte[], int[], String

    Data can be retrieved using getValue(), set using setValue() and added using addValue()
    The value setting and adding methods also accept tags, both NBTBase and CommonTag
    The set/get/add methods operate on CommonTag instances only and can generally be ignored

      • setAllValues

        public <T> void setAllValues(T... values)
        Clears all values contained and sets the contents to the data specified. Collections, arrays (also primitive) and maps are supported for data types. Other data types are added as a single element, and may cause an exception if not supported.

        The individual elements can be collections or arrays as well, which allows adding multiple arrays at once.
